==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emolument
<hw>E*mol"u*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>emolumentum</ets>, lit., a working out, fr. <ets>emoliri</ets> to
move out, work out; <ets>e</ets> out + <ets>moliri</ets> to set in
motion, exert one's self, fr. <ets>moles</ets> a huge, heavy mass: cf.
F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧molument</ets>. See <er>Mole</er> a mound.]</ety>
<def>The profit arising from office, employment, or labor; gain;
compensation; advantage; perquisites, fees, or salary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A long . . . enjoyment of the <qex>emoluments</qex> of office.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emolumental</ent>⟦br⟧
